<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2866&amp;p=13603#p13603"><![CDATA[
Classic Explorer has two features that affect software outside of Windows Explorer. One is showing the &quot;shared folder&quot; overlay in the shell, and the other is a replacement for the copy files dialog. The second feature is only for Windows 7.<br />If you don't need those two then you can certainly uninstall that component. Your selection will be remembered for the next time you update Classic Shell to a new version.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Sat Jun 28, 2014 8:57 pm</p><hr />
